<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,578,2029]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Female macropterous (
<figureCitation box="[425,516,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 37. H" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[298,1287,193,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[249,1338,176,1721]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 37. H. pilarae: 33 Female; 34 Male. H. stellae: 35 Female; 36 Male. 37 H.? flavitibia" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[482,516,578,604]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
): 
<emphasis box="[539,608,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Color</emphasis>
: Body uniformly brown., fore tibiae, apex of fore femur and all tarsi yellowish, antennal segments I and II dark brown, apex of II, segment III and IV yellowish brown, V–IX brown (
<figureCitation box="[242,313,651,677]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,313,651,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); forewing shaded greyish brown with basal 
<number box="[841,856,651,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[865,878,651,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
clearer (
<figureCitation box="[981,1068,651,677]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 32. H" captionStartId="8.[151,270,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[228,1364,195,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[192,1395,176,1853]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 32. H. marginatus: 24 tergite. H. moestus: 25 tergite. H. pilarae: 26 Sternites. H. cacti: 27 Sternites; 28 Antenna. H. myrceugenellae: 29. Antennal segment III – IV. H. pilarae: 30 Antennal segments III – IV; 31 Right forewing. H. stellae: 32 Right forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197148/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1036,1068,651,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,578,2029]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[197,307,688,713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Structure</emphasis>
: Head (
<figureCitation box="[408,472,688,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[461,472,688,714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) wider than long and broader at base, with three pairs of ocellar setae, pair III arising between the lines that connect fore and hind ocelli; with five pairs of postocular setae, three arising near to hind ocelli and two near to cheek. Antennal segment III tripartite with short pedicel; segments III and IV with a sensorial band, apparently a simple row of pores at apex (
<figureCitation box="[979,1055,797,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1037,1055,797,823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.3">2</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1068,1103,797,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 32. H" captionStartId="8.[151,270,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[228,1364,195,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[192,1395,176,1853]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 32. H. marginatus: 24 tergite. H. moestus: 25 tergite. H. pilarae: 26 Sternites. H. cacti: 27 Sternites; 28 Antenna. H. myrceugenellae: 29. Antennal segment III – IV. H. pilarae: 30 Antennal segments III – IV; 31 Right forewing. H. stellae: 32 Right forewing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197148/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">30</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with transverse sculpture lines and about 
<number box="[466,496,834,860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="34.0">34</number>
discal setae (
<figureCitation box="[665,731,834,860]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[720,731,834,860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum with transverse lines and with pair of more developed setae placed at posterior third of sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[789,864,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[847,864,871,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Metanotum with concentric lines of structure covered with microtrichia, with two pairs of setae, the external pair located at anterior margin and the inner pair at posterior margin, campaniform sensilla present (
<figureCitation box="[802,873,944,970]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[857,873,944,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tergites (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1111,944,970]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6. H" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[191,1394,469,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,469,2012]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. H. pilarae: 1 Head and Pronotum; 2 Antenna; 3 Meso and Metanotum; 4 Tergites V – VI; 5 Tergites IX –" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/197146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Figs 
<number box="[1066,1111,944,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="4.5">4, 5</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[1125,1171,944,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.9">8, 9</number>
, 
<number box="[1184,1256,944,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="10.11">10, 11</number>
and 
<number box="[1314,1344,944,970]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="12.0">12</number>
) II–VII with one pair of well developed setae medially, with reticulation at middle zone and more strongly on lateral third, with several discal setae laterally. Tergites II–VIII with microtrichia at posterior margin, forming a complete comb on tergites VI–VIII, the rest of these tergites with microtrichia at middle and laterally on posterior margin; tergites VIII–IX with discal microtrichia. Sternites (Figs 
<number box="[1060,1122,1090,1116]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="7.26">7, 26</number>
) with weak reticulation, I with minute setae at anterior ridge, II–VI with spaced setae and microtrichia on posterior margin, VII with few short microtrichia arising at posterior margin. Pleurites II–VII with posteromaginal microtrichia. Some specimens presented anomalies, such as the first tergite with only one seta medially; the comb of microtrichia on tergite VI is variable, sometimes incomplete.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
